<!-- 1.2.40 -->
<div class="toload definition">
<p><span class="envidentifier">Definition 1.2.40
<span style="font-weight:normal;">([<span class='ref' data-tag='MR1940513'></span>, p. 82])</span></span>
Let $\kappa$ be a cardinal. An inverse semigroup $S$ is <em>$\kappa$-distributive</em> if for every compatible set $F\subseteq S$ with $|F|<\kappa$, the supremum $\bigvee F$ exists and for all $z\in S$,
<div class="equation"\[
z\left(\bigvee F\right)=\bigvee(zF).
\]</div>
Note that $|zF|\leq |F|$ and $zF$ is compatible by Proposition <span class='ref' data-tag='propositioncompatibility'></span>, and that $\left(\bigvee F\right)z=\bigvee(Fz)$ also holds by Proposition <span class='ref' data-tag='propositionpropertiesofjoins'></span>(b).
</p>
</div>